      "PowerShell(git commit -m \"fix: reliable platform title counts + non-empty watch pages\" -m \"The /watch/:platform query asked for count:exact alongside a 1000-row select over the unindexed streaming_links JSON filter \\(~3.1s\\), which exceeded the statement timeout under load and threw, blanking the page \\(e.g. /watch/ebonylife showed empty despite 41 films\\). Now fetch films without the exact count \\(~1.2s, with retry\\) and load the count separately as a non-blocking best-effort, so a slow count can never blank the grid.\" -m \"Also defer the homepage platform-tile counts until after the main load burst clears so they stop timing out and getting stuck on 'Browse'.\" -m \"Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\")",
